claim.claim-text:
1. A multi-band receiving terminal of a mobile communications system, comprising: 
a filter unit which filters signals in each of a plurality of frequency bands; 
an impedance-matching unit which matches impedance of signals output from the filter unit along each of said plurality of frequency bands; 
a switching unit which selects a signal output from the impedance-matching unit based on which of said plurality of frequency bands a received signal belongs; and 
an RF receiver which receives the signal selected by the switching unit.

6. An apparatus for a triple band receiving terminal of a mobile communication system, comprising: 
a first filter for passing signals corresponding to a first band; 
a second filter for passing signals corresponding to a second band; 
a third filter for passing signals corresponding to a third band; 
an impedance matching unit for matching impedance of signals passing the second and the third filters; and 
a RF (radio frequency) receiver for processing signals inputted from the first filter and a switching unit as an intermediate frequency.

10. The apparatus of claim 6, wherein the RF receiver comprises: 
an amplifier for amplifying a reception signal inputted through the first filter and the switching unit at a predetermined level; 
a local oscillator for generating and outputting an oscillation frequency; 
a first and a second phase shifters for receiving the oscillation frequency from the local oscillator and phase-modulating the oscillation frequency; and 
a mixer for outputting an intermediate frequency by mixing the signals outputted from the first and the second phase shifters with the signal outputted from the amplifier.

15. An apparatus for a triple band receiving terminal of a mobile communication system, comprising: 
a first, a second, and a third filters for filtering signals in a first, a second and a third bands; 
a first and a second matching units for impedance-matching the signals passing the second and the third filters; 
a switching unit for selectively connecting to the first or the second matching unit; 
a first and a second low noise amplifiers for amplifying signals inputted from the first filter and the switching unit at a predetermined level; 
a first and a second phase shifters for phase-modulating an oscillation frequency outputted from the local oscillator; 
a first and a second mixers for mixing an output signal of the first low noise amplifier with the oscillation frequency outputted from the first phase shifter; and 
a third and a fourth mixers for mixing an output signal of the second low noise amplifier with the oscillation frequency outputted from the second phase shifter.

26. A method for processing signals in a mobile communication system, comprising: 
providing an impedance-matching unit which matches impedances of signals within at least two frequency bands; 
determining in which of said two frequency bands a received signal belongs; 
inputting the received signal into the impedance-matching unit; and 
selecting an output of the impedance-matching unit based on the frequency band of the received signal.

27. The method of claim 26, further comprising: 
generating an oscillation signal based on the frequency band of the received signal; 
mixing the oscillation signal with the output of the impedance-matching unit selected in said selecting step.
